This paper focuses on deep learning methods for image clustering, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel clustering framework that involves exploring various kinds of correlations in the data, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of pseudo-label supervision and triplet mutual information, which suggests that it may be relevant to the natural language processing (cs.CL) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
